Commentary: low full toss on off stump, mistimes his drive to cover
Commentary_short: Devcich to Simmons, no run

Commentary: good length outside off, no real spin, just inward drift in the air. Cut off the back foot towards cover point
Commentary_short: Devcich to Simmons, no run

Commentary: driven! Excellent short to get off the mark. Full stride forward and driven between cover and cover point. Races away
Commentary_short: Devcich to Simmons, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length outside off, cuts off the back foot to cover point. Too close to his body for that shot
Commentary_short: Devcich to Simmons, no run

Commentary: full and wide this time, caresses this drive between cover and point. Baz the man giving the chase, but his age has caught up. The delivery wins the race to the cover-point boundary
Commentary_short: Devcich to Simmons, FOUR runs

Commentary: full and wide outside off, that's three for the over! Driven once again, and beats the four infielders on the off side. This time it goes past cover's left
Commentary_short: Devcich to Simmons, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on middle, goes deep onto the back foot and turns it off his hips to midwicket
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Denly, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, angles into the batsman and traps him on his crease. Manages to inside edge his defense towards the leg side
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Simmons, 2 runs

Commentary: good length just outside off, mistimes his back-foot punch to mid on for hurried run
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: goes short on off stump, and this time he bowls it from near the crease. Denly shuffles towards off and flicks to midwicket
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Denly, 1 run

Commentary: back of the hander slower ball, but it's not well executed. Full toss on off stump, but deceived enough to mistime his drive. Bunted to cover
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: another back of the hand, full on off stump. Drives to mid on, but not timed well. Enough to take the single though
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Denly, 1 run

Commentary: out first ball! Flighted full on off stump and turns away. Entices Denly to drive, and it's hit uppishly. Baz at short cover. Takes a small jump and collects this from above his head. Big wicket
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Denly, OUT
Dismissal_text: JL Denly c McCullum b Yasir Shah 3 (4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 75.00

Commentary: good length on off stump, can't time his back-foot punch well. Off the bat's top half, and the pull has been dropped by Afridi. Oh dear. He blames the lights. Gives Babar a life
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: good length on middle, turned towards the leg side
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Babar Azam, no run
Yasir Shah to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, Simmons comes down the wicket but checks his shot. Looks to defend and comes off the bat-pad
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Simmons, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, times his drive well, but straight to mid off. Babar wants the run, but Simmons is quick to send him back. The throw's good, and Yasir takes the bails off, but looks like he broke it with his hand. Babar would've probably been safe anyway
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Simmons, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, sharp spin inwards and almost goes down the leg side. Simmons tried to flick towards the leg side, but the ball hits his pads
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: good length just outside off, goes deep into the crease and punched off the back foot past cover point
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: appeal for stumping! Did his back leg slide out. Good length on off stump, and misses his drive because of the extra bounce. Quick work from the keeper. Looks like it's on the line. Should be interesting.
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Simmons, no run

Commentary: full on middle stump, mistimes his drive down the ground and it's intercepted by Yasir. Direct hit at the non-striker's but Simmons is in.
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: cuts him in half! Full on middle stump, comes slightly inwards and the ball goes between bat and pad, as he tries to drive. Just past the outside of off stump
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: finds the gap on the off side! Full on off, and enough room to free his arms. Driven with the bat's open face, and breaches the gap between point and cover point
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on middle stump, turns inwards and hits his pads
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, no run

Commentary: full and wide outside off, driven off the back foot past cover. Good use of his wrists to play square
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length outside off and turns inwards. Simmons misses the slog, and the ball's into the keeper's gloves. Is he stumped? That was close, but Simmons back leg was just inside the line
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, no run

Commentary: good length on off stump, turned towards the leg side
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, 2 runs

Commentary: good length outside off, opens his bat's face and runs it down past short third man. Beats the infield!
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on off stump, big stride forward and driven to mid off. Stopped by Yasir
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, angles across him, and tapped towards cover point. Played with soft hands
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full outside leg, it's the slower ball to start off. Simmons gives it a big wind up, but adjusts his shot to the pace. Pushed awkwardly to mid off
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: full on leg stump, stays on the back foot, and defended to mid on
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full on middle stump, walks across to the off side, and flicked past square leg! Elegant looking this time, and played nice and fine
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on off stump, drives well, but straight to cover. Babar rues missing out
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: makes up this time! It's full outside off, and the drive goes through the gap. Races into the extra-cover boundary
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: full outside off, and the batsman is deceived completely. Misses the drive as the ball goes past his outside edge, but so does the keeper. The turn's too much for either of them
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Simmons, 4 byes

Commentary: full on off stump, driven to mid on off the front foot. Not hit well enough, and allows them to take the run
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle stump, prods forward and turns it off his pads to the leg side. Comfortably gets off strike
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full outside off, stays on the back foot and cuts this fine. Beats short third man but he's giving it a chase. Almost wins it, but his acrobatic somersault from Agha can't parry the ball back. Gets an applause from Yasir for the effort
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Simmons, FOUR runs

Commentary: over long on! Full on leg stump, but Simmons dances down the wicket, gets his front foot out of the way, and smacks it into the second tier
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Simmons, SIX runs

Commentary: good length wide outside off, quick to get to the back foot and cut fine. Past backward point's left, and races away for a boundary
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Simmons, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on middle and leg, a quick shuffle towards the off side and clipped off his toes to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: short on middle stump, forces Simmons to tiptoe. Glanced off the back foot to backward point. They walk across for the run
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, angling across the batsman, and chopped down to third man. He's happy to give the strike back to Simmons
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, Simmons is quick to swivel, and it's pulled along the carpet to deep midwicket. The man's there, but the ball's always going away from him
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Simmons, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length on leg stump, nudged off the back foot to midwicket
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: goes between the keeper and first slip! It's the offcutter, and Babar's deceived. Sticks his bat out, and it's edged. Falls short of the two men behind the stumps, but bounces through both their dives. Babar acknowledges the ball's difficulty with a grin
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: full just outside off, sees the ball through, and defended towards point with the bat's open face
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, no run

Commentary: good length on off stump, spins inwards and flicked off his pads to square leg. They walk across for the run and that's his fifty!
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, drives down the ground, but comes off the bat's inside half. Through to wide long on
Commentary_short: Narine to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: pitched full on leg stump, walks in front and tucked off his toes to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle and off, nudges it with the spin to deep midwicket. Babar wants the second, but Simmons wants to stay on strike
Commentary_short: Narine to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle stump, and spins inwards. Simmons is trapped on the crease, and hits his pads. The keeper is quick to dive forward and collect the ball. Looks for the run-out, but Simmons' back leg is well in
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, no run

Commentary: full on middle stump, driven to mid on comfortably, but it's a direct hit at the non-striker's! Babar's safe
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle and leg, pulled along the ground to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle and leg, defended off the back foot, and sent back to the bowler
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full on leg stump, tries to flick towards the leg side, but takes the leading edge to cover. Slower ball, too
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: short on off stump, and that takes an extra bounce! Simmons lines up for the big slash over third man, but can't connect. Looks like he went too hard at that shot
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Simmons, no run

Commentary: slower bouncer! Simmons misses out once again. Short on middle stump. Simmons comes down the wicket, but can't connect with his pull. The ball goes under his bat
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Simmons, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, big stride forward and driven. To mid off, though
Commentary_short: Narine to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full on middle stump, shuffles towards the right and smothers it with the spin to square leg
Commentary_short: Narine to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside off, spins into him, and punched towards cover point. They scamper across for the run
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: full just outside off, spins into Babar, and he nudges it with soft hands towards the leg side
Commentary_short: Narine to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full and wide outside off, big stride forward and flicked off his pads to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Narine to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full outside off, spins away from Simmons this time, and driven square off the front foot. To the square-fielder in the deep
Commentary_short: Narine to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: short outside off, angles into Simmons, and he flat-bats it towards cow corner from over his head
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Simmons, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, pulls down the ground to long on. Bunts it, really
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: holes out to McClenaghan! A brilliant diving catch at long on sends Simmons back. Full on leg stump, and Simmons tries to thump this over Sohail's head. But it's the slower ball, and Simmons simply bottom edges it
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Simmons, OUT
Dismissal_text: LMP Simmons c McClenaghan b Sohail Khan 55 (39b 8x4 1x6) SR: 141.02

Commentary: starts off with a dot. It's full and wide outside off, and tapped with soft hands to sweeper cover
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Ingram, 1 run

Commentary: yorker on middle, but manages to get his bat down, and squeeze this to deep backward square
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Babar Azam, 2 runs

Commentary: just short of full on off stump, comfortably flicked to deep midwicket. He'll keep strike
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, legspin. Babar goes deep into the crease and drags his pull to cow corner
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full just outside off stump, smacks this down the ground to long on
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Ingram, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, Babar comes down the wicket and mistimes his drive. Bat-padded to Yasir
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, big heave towards the leg side, but doesn't have the distance. In fact, that saves Babar. Drops between wide long on and deep midwicket. Fakhar didn't charge in quick enough
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, turning away from Ingram, and he carves it off the back foot to deep backward point
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Ingram, 1 run

Commentary: too full for the pull. Pitches on off stump, but he bunts this towards the leg side. Bottom edges the pull shot to the deep
Commentary_short: Yasir Shah to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside leg, but angling into the batsman. Flicked off his waist to cow corner. They walk across for the run
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: yorker on middle and leg, manages to squeeze it down to the leg side. Deep backward square cleaning up this time
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Ingram, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, stands tall and punches inside out to Fakhar at mid off. Misfielded though! Quite a powerful shot, to be fair, but the ball pops out of the fielder's hands. Adds to McClenaghan's frustrations
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: dropped by Sohail in the deep! Can't collect it on the rebound. Short on off and Ingram pulls this to deep backward square, Sohail's far too inside the rope, and hits his hand, but the ball falls behind him thereafter. How costly will that be?
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Ingram, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, slower this time, and his off-side heave over cover doesn't connect. Goes through to the keeper
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: good length on middle and leg, pulled along the ground to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: McClenaghan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length just outside off, carved off the back foot to deep extra cover
Commentary_short: Narine to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, turns away from the left-hander, pokes at it towards cover
Commentary_short: Narine to Ingram, no run

Commentary: good length on off, and grips away from Ingram. Tries to punch it away, but misses. Through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Narine to Ingram, no run

Commentary: short on off stump, enough time this time to carve off the back foot to deep backward point
Commentary_short: Narine to Ingram, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle stump, he's trapped on his crease, but manages to get bat to ball. Nudged towards the leg side
Commentary_short: Narine to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: good length on leg stump, spins into Ingram on this occasion, and flicked towards deep square leg
Commentary_short: Narine to Ingram, 1 run

Commentary: low full toss on middle stump to start off, muscles his drive down the ground, but only to mid off
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Ingram, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, and it's shoveled! Smacked past the umpire's length, and races away to the long-on boundary. Uses the bottom hand so well, this fella
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Ingram, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on off and middle again, but Ingram can't get the same connection. Mistimes his drive to mid on, who races to his right and intercepts
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Ingram, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, always angling across Babar, so he gives it a wild slash. Wants to hit it over cover, but it comes off the bat's bottom end. Goes fine to the third-man boundary
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: Mid off dives over the ball! McCullum the guilty man here. Has he hurt his shoulder? It was full on off stump, but Babar muscles this down the ground. Hit well, and Baz got to the ball, but couldn't pull the execution off
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on off stump, angling into the batsman, and pulled to deep backward square
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball, short on middle stump. Smothers this to square leg, but the diving effort stops the ball. Can't stop the single, though. Fifty for Babar!
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: well deceived! The slower ball from Sohail does the trick once again. Back of the hand, and full on off stump. Tries to slog it towards cow corner, but it's sliced. Up in the air, and taken by the keeper. Big wicket in the end overs
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Ingram, OUT
Dismissal_text: CA Ingram c †Gulraiz Sadaf b Sohail Khan 12 (13b 1x4 0x6) SR: 92.30

Commentary: short and wide outside off, opens the bat's face and slices this over point! Controlled shot, and sent over the boundary!
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Babar Azam, SIX runs

Commentary: short outside off, and it's the slower bouncer this time. Drags his pull from over his head to cow corner
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, tails into the batsman. Tapped to cover for a quick single
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Bopara, 1 run

Commentary: full on leg stump, slower ball once again. Driven with the bat's closed face to wide long on. Fakhar the man there
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Babar Azam, 2 runs

Commentary: full just outside off stump, tries to drive down the ground, but misses. Past the bat's outside edge
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bopara, no run

Commentary: yorker on leg stump, but angling down the leg side. Goes through to the keeper, and Bopara is bemused that it's not called a wide. Was there a touch off his boot? Bopara doesn't seem to think so
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bopara, no run

Commentary: short on off stump, charges down the wicket and tries to slash at it. Mistimed towards deep point
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bopara, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, pulled with the ball angling into him. Hit over the square-leg umpire to Mitch in the deep
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full on leg stump, through his flick too soon. Off the bat's top half, and trickles down to deep backward square
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bopara, 1 run

Commentary: yorker on leg stump. Babar can't get bat to ball, but the ball was angling down always. Hits his pad and the ball dribbles away to square leg
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Babar Azam, 1 leg bye

Commentary: starts off with a yorker. On leg stump, and bottom edged down to fine leg
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: knee-high full toss on off stump, enough room for Bopara to thump this over the leg side. Got his front foot out of the way, and slogs it to cow corner
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Bopara, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length outside off, too close to Bopara for the back-foot punch but the luck's with him! Takes the outside edge, and past the keeper's right. Races away!
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Bopara, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on off stump, tries to cut off the back foot, but he''s deceived by the slower ball. Bottom edges it to the keeper
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Bopara, no run

Commentary: good length on off stump, drags his pull to deep backward square on this occasion
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Bopara, 1 run

Commentary: holes out to long off! Another slower-ball wicket to Sohail's kitty. Tries to slog it down the ground, but the bat turns in his hand. Perishes for 61
Commentary_short: Sohail Khan to Babar Azam, OUT
Dismissal_text: Babar Azam c Narine b Sohail Khan 61 (49b 6x4 1x6) SR: 124.48

Commentary: full outside leg stump, but it's too quick for Bopara to get his feet out of the way. Hits his pad, and trickles down to the leg side
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bopara, 1 leg bye

Commentary: boom boom! First-ball six from Afridi! Oh man, and that's been smacked over long on. Slower ball on off stump, and it's been muscled. Picked the slower ball early and dispatched. The spectators are delighted!
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Shahid Afridi, SIX runs

Commentary: out second ball! Six and out, and that's an excellent second ball. Full on middle, and the batsman misses the slog. The middle stump is on the ground and Shaheen - presumably out of respect - pulls out of his celebration. Guess the bowler won the Afridi battle?
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Shahid Afridi, OUT
Dismissal_text: Shahid Afridi  b Shaheen Shah Afridi 6 (2b 0x4 1x6) SR: 300.00

Commentary: full on off stump, Imad backs away to the leg side and slaps it to cover. Managed to make the room, but just couldn't find the gap
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Imad Wasim, 1 run

Commentary: expensive! Good length on leg stump, but wayward. Goes down the leg side with Bopara trying to flick it fine. The keeper's dive to the left ain't good enough either. He's got to bowl that one again
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bopara, 5 wides

Commentary: full on off stump, stands tall and bunts it down to long on. Only a single
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bopara, 1 run

Commentary: tries the reverse paddle, but Imad can't connect. Full ball on middle, and the ball hits his boot and through to the off side. McCullum wants to review - probably just because they can. Can Shaheen get another wicket? It hits the pad low in front of leg stump, but looks like it'll miss the leg side. Yes, it does. Karachi finish on 163 for 5
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Imad Wasim, 1 leg bye

Commentary: good length wide outside off, and it's the one that angles just a bit away. Fakhar lets it go through after offering his bat for a moment
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: full on off stump, tapped off the front foot to mid on for a quick single
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, angling into his pads, and smothered past square leg. Races away, such beautiful timing
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Devcich, FOUR runs

Commentary: short and wide outside off, tries to cut, but no timing behind that. Bottom edged towards point
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Devcich, no run

Commentary: slower-ball yorker on off stump. Manages to nudge it towards deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Devcich, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, angling into Fakhar, and defended off the back foot
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: good length outside off, it's the slider that jags into the left hander. Goes deep onto the back foot, and punched past the bowler's right
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Devcich, no run

Commentary: full toss on middle stump, thumped towards midwicket, but the man's positioned there
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Devcich, no run

Commentary: short on off stump, stands tall and pulls off the back foot. Hit quite straight, in fact. Goes past mid on's left
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Devcich, FOUR runs

Commentary: full outside off, too wide, and it's been slashed past Simmons at point. The diving effort was just not good enough. Can't give Devcich any width
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Devcich, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on middle stump, turned off his toes to deep backward square. Helps the quick ball on its way
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Devcich, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, jags into Fakhar, and he tries the pull shot. Misses out, however. Bottom edged onto his pads
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: hits him where it hurts the most! Devcich is down on his knees. Good length outside off, and the extra bounce brings the delivery ball. He misses the leg-side slog. Here's hoping that abdomen guard is high quality. We need a breather
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Devcich, no run

Commentary: quick from Amir! Good length on middle stump, tucked towards the leg side or a quick run. Amir was swift to run down the wicket and lob the ball onto the stumps at the striker's end. Fakhar's dive saves him
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Devcich, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, flicked off his pads towards midwicket for a walking single
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full on leg stump, backs away towards the leg side and smacks it past Amir! He puts his hand out to the right, and gets fingertips to it. Ooo, it's bleeding! Full marks for commitment, but blood is never nice. Hit so hard, that mid off had no chance either. Lucky for Karachi, that's his right hand
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Devcich, FOUR runs

Commentary: ramped over the keeper! Back of a length ball and angling into Devcich. Backs away to the off side, and lifts if over the keeper's head. Excellent
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Devcich, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length on middle, tucked to square leg off the back foot, and finally, that's the end of the over
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Devcich, 1 run

Commentary: another first-ball wicket! Full outside leg stump, Devcich misses the leg-side flick but the ball hits his pad and ricochets onto middle stump. Goes after a breezy 24
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Devcich, OUT
Dismissal_text: AP Devcich  b Mohammad Irfan 24 (14b 5x4 0x6) SR: 171.42

Commentary: good length on off stump, angling into the right hander, extra bounce this time, and hits his guts. The ball trickles towards the off side
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Agha Salman, no run

Commentary: full outside off, and it's the textbook cover drive. Full extension of the arms and sent to the extra-cover boundary
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Agha Salman, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length outside off, stands tall and cuts to point. Well hit, but no direction in that
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Agha Salman, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, but angling down the leg side. Comfortably glanced off his pads past short fine leg. No stopping that! Just a bit awry, that line
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Agha Salman, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length wide outside off, angling into Salman and carved to deep backward point
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Agha Salman, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, chops it down to third man and they're off for the second run. Irfan, from third man, runs to his left and does an excellent pick-up-and-throw to the keeper. But the keeper misses the run out! Threw it at the stumps from a couple of feet away, but misses. Fakhar's hurt his knee, and Irfan may also have hurt his finger
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Agha Salman, 2 runs

Commentary: good length on off stump, angles into the batsman's body. Punched off the back foot square on the off side
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Agha Salman, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, flat-bats this slower ball to wide long on. Mistimes his slog

Commentary: yorker just outside leg stump, Hits his boot. Tried to use his wrists to flick fine, but couldn't get bat to ball
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to McCullum, no run

Commentary: overpitched full and very wide outside off stump. Baz doesn't even bother moving. Gotta bowl that again

Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to McCullum, no run

Commentary: low full toss on middle and leg, clipped to deep midwicket. That's the first ball he managed to get his bat to the delivery
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to McCullum, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle and off, caresses this drive to cover for a single. There's his fifty! An excellent knock, but the job is only half done
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Agha Salman, 1 run

Commentary: yorker on off stump. Bottom edges it to mid off for a run
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to McCullum, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, angling across BMac, and he smacks it (flat-batted, really) to cover
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to McCullum, no run

Commentary: classic Baz! Six over the keeper's head. We've missed that ramp shot from the man. Full toss on middle stump, and McCullum shuffles to the off side, opens his stance, and scoops it over the keeper. Oh, my, my.
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to McCullum, SIX runs

Commentary: full on leg stump. McCullium tries to turn this towards square leg, but can't connect. Hits his boot and trickles down to short fine leg
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to McCullum, 1 leg bye

Commentary: short on leg stump. Big wind up, and pulls it off the back foot! Looks like it's going for a six, but nope! Babar Azam at deep midwicket, takes the catch, but scoops it back before going over the rope. Lendl Simmons is nearby, and he holds on to Babar's lob. The umpire wants a second look: the replays suggest that Babar's toe wasn't touching the rope at all. Excellent from him. The replays have been one for atleast three minutes now. What's the decision? Out! Take nothing away from Salman, though. A brilliant innings comes to an end.
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Agha Salman, OUT
Dismissal_text: Agha Salman c Simmons b Usman Shinwari 50 (45b 4x4 1x6) SR: 111.11

Commentary: full toss on middle and leg, nudged off his pads to deep midwicket. Calls for the second run early and completed with ease
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to McCullum, 2 runs

Commentary: clipped to square leg! Usman Khan you beauty. Full on leg stump, and turned to the only infielder on the leg side. Simple catch to Simmons. A double fist-pump from the bowler as BMac makes his way back
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to McCullum, OUT

Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Sohail Akhtar, 1 run

Commentary: knee-high full toss outside off stump, sliced over mid off, but it's in the air! Imad Wasim runs backward before taking a catch from near his face. Comes down tumbling - on his back - and completes an excellent catch. Hopefully he hasn't hurt his head. Came down with quite a mighty force there. Imad Wasim has been stretchered off.

Dismissal_text: Sohail Khan c Imad Wasim b Mohammad Amir 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: good length on middle stump, punched off the back foot to cover point
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Sohail Akhtar, 1 run

Commentary: Ramps it fine! Full outside off, shuffles across to the off side and paddles over the keeper. Fine leg was too square
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to McClenaghan, FOUR runs

Commentary: short on off stump, McClenaghan tries the reverse paddle this time, but can't connect. Awkward bounce for the keeper, and he misses the collection. Allows them to steal the run
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to McClenaghan, 1 bye

Commentary: full on off stump, tries to flick towards square leg but misses. Hits his back leg, and dribbles away to the leg side. The keeper chases behind it, but McClenaghan could be in trouble! Nope, he's safe. The fielder from midwicket took the bails off, but the big New Zealander was in
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Sohail Akhtar, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, manages to shovel it to point. The fielder has a shy at the stumps but misses. No one backing up, and Sohail comes back for the second run
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Sohail Akhtar, 2 runs

Commentary: smacked over Usman! Stands tall and pitches this full ball's length very early. Big swing, and he misses the yorker. The low full toss comes off the bat's sweet spot
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Sohail Akhtar, FOUR runs

Commentary: you beauty, Sohail Akhtar! Full on off stump, and he gets his front foot out of the way. Just the perfect length for the long handle, and it's been thumped over long off. Smoked!
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Sohail Akhtar, SIX runs

Commentary: short ball on middle stump, tries to pull but misses because of the slower ball. McClenaghan is backing up and he's scampered across to the other side, but the keeper gets the direct hit. They're taking the second run - off the overthrow - but replays show that the batsman was short! Dot ball, and Sohail's off strike. Four off two now
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Sohail Akhtar, OUT
Dismissal_text: MJ McClenaghan run out (†Mohammad Rizwan) 4 (2b 1x4 0x6) SR: 200.00

Commentary: full on off stump, smacked to cover for a single. They need three off the final ball to win. Two for a super over
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Gulraiz Sadaf, 1 run

Commentary: is that a six?! Nope, that's taken at long on! But wait, he's overstepped! Karachi's celebrations need to wait. It was in the slot to be punished, and Sohail lifts this over the non-striker and taken at long on. Karachi are celebrating, but, but, but, but, Usman has conceded a front-foot no ball! You can't write a script for this! Free hit now, but they're also checking if the batsmen took a single before the catch was taken. If they complete the run then Lahore will need 1 off 1. If he was out before the run was taken, then Lahore need 2 off 1. The umpires are still conferring. OK, its official: no run off the bat there. Lahore need two off one. Plus, a free hit. They can only be run out off the last ball.
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Sohail Akhtar, 1 no ball

Commentary: super over! Unbelievable scenes. Confusion everywhere. Full toss low on middle stump, mistimed to the leg side and they're off for the run. Usman collects, and runs them out at the striker's end as they try to sneak a second. McCullum and Lahore want clarification. He's talking to the umpire, presumably about the run off the previous delivery. The commentators say that 'McCullum thought that they needed one off the final ball.' There's still a lot of confusion, but sanity prevails eventually. It'll be a super over. Phew.
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Gulraiz Sadaf, 1 run, OUT
Dismissal_text: Gulraiz Sadaf run out (Usman Shinwari/†Mohammad Rizwan) 2 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 100.00
